content.description: Start on the east side down low. Make a dynamic move to a crimp. Set your feet, grab some jugs, and top out.
content.protection: A pad is nice. A spotter is not really necessary.

content.description: On the west side of the Barbwire Boulder.  Starts on sloper and hold way under bulge.  moves up the sloper rail and ends on the ledge to the left of the slopers.
content.protection: Just need a good spot to keep from hitting the barbwire.

content.description: Located at they barbwire boulder down the hill. On the north side starts on a small pebble and a small ledge.  Moves up to a slopy ledge. Use the angled arete to get around the corner. and top it out.
content.protection: Crash pad is Recomended but not nessicary.  Only need a good spot

content.description: It is on the first large set of cliffs you go down.  The route is on a 20 ft cliff meet at a 90 degree angle by another rock.  There is a large hand crack right at the angle.  Going up the crack is a v2.  Without using the crack and using the the four finger pocket is a v3. Dynoing from the rail about 2/3 of the way up to the top is a v5. Be careful!  There is a reason it is called Ankle Breaker.
content.protection: Need at least 2 thick pads and two good spotters
